
Define an extended macro without default parameters:
  Input: |-
    {@define [named]w(a,b,c)=.a b c.}{w}
    {w a=XXX}
    {w b=XXX}
    {w c=XXX}
    {w a=XXX b=YYY c=ZZZ}
  Output: |-
    .  .
    .XXX  .
    . XXX .
    .  XXX.
    .XXX YYY ZZZ.

Define an extended macro with default parameters:
  Input: |-
    {@define [defaults="""
    a=AAA
    b=BBB
    c=CCC
    """]w(a,b,c)=a b c}{w}
    {w a=XXX}
    {w b=XXX}
    {w c=XXX}
    {w a=XXX b=YYY c=ZZZ}
  Output: |-
    AAA BBB CCC
    XXX BBB CCC
    AAA XXX CCC
    AAA BBB XXX
    XXX YYY ZZZ
